01:48.304 --> 01:50.738
<i>It's bad enough I'm being taken</i>

01:50.739 --> 01:51.883
against my will.

01:51.885 --> 01:53.285
I don't see why it has to be in

01:53.287 --> 01:55.187
some hippie's
mobile sex dungeon.

01:56.656 --> 01:58.624
Well, Sheldon,
there's something about this van

01:58.626 --> 02:00.726
that you're going to find
very interesting.

02:00.728 --> 02:03.528
It runs on syphilis?

02:05.064 --> 02:08.166
This van was owned
and driven by your personal

02:08.168 --> 02:09.501
physics hero...

02:09.502 --> 02:11.068
Richard Feynman.

02:11.071 --> 02:12.971
No.
Yeah!

02:12.973 --> 02:14.740
A buddy of mine
let me borrow it.

02:14.742 --> 02:16.508
This was Feynman's van?

02:16.510 --> 02:17.676
That's so cool.

02:17.678 --> 02:19.311
Yeah, nothing's been changed
since he drove it.

02:19.313 --> 02:22.014
I bet he picked up a lot of cute
grad students in this bad boy.

02:22.016 --> 02:24.049
Yeah, and talked about physics
with them!

02:26.453 --> 02:28.453
So, are you gonna give us
a clue where we're headed?

02:28.455 --> 02:31.390
Uh, okay, let's see...

02:31.392 --> 02:33.058
They've got spicy food

02:33.060 --> 02:36.061
and there's a chance
you'll get diarrhea.

02:36.063 --> 02:39.398
India.

02:39.400 --> 02:41.533
We can drive there.

02:41.535 --> 02:43.368
Your house?

02:44.937 --> 02:47.539
We are going
to Meh-he-co!

02:47.541 --> 02:48.707
Fun, I've never been there!

02:48.709 --> 02:50.542
Leonard, don't be fooled!

02:50.544 --> 02:51.843
I'm from Texas--

02:51.845 --> 02:55.313
Meh-he-co is Spanish for Mexico.

02:55.315 --> 02:57.215
What's wrong with Mexico?

02:57.217 --> 02:59.885
Uh, mariachi bands, wild dogs,

02:59.887 --> 03:03.221
beans that jump around
'cause there's a worm inside.

03:03.223 --> 03:04.856
Okay, calm down.

03:04.858 --> 03:06.124
There's a theme
to this weekend.

03:06.126 --> 03:09.695
We are going to Mexico
in Feynman's van

03:09.697 --> 03:12.164
to stay at the vacation house
Feynman bought

03:12.166 --> 03:14.032
with the money
from his Nobel Prize.

03:14.034 --> 03:15.667
<i>Viva la Imodium!</i>

03:15.669 --> 03:17.202
<i>Ay-ay-ay!</i>

03:20.273 --> 03:22.708
Come on, Leonard's
doing bachelor stuff.

03:22.710 --> 03:24.443
You sure we can't take
you to a strip club?

03:24.445 --> 03:27.145
Nah, if I want to see
a naked dancing man,

03:27.147 --> 03:29.081
I just flush the toilet
while Leonard's in the shower.

03:32.218 --> 03:34.653
Hi.
Hey.

03:34.655 --> 03:36.755
I know we're not making a fuss,

03:36.757 --> 03:39.691
but in the spirit
of bachelorette parties,

03:39.693 --> 03:43.061
I made cookies in the
shape of male genitals.

03:44.130 --> 03:46.031
You really
didn't have to...

03:46.033 --> 03:47.933
Whoa!

03:48.901 --> 03:51.269
That is anatomic.

03:51.271 --> 03:52.437
Thank you.

03:52.439 --> 03:54.406
The veins are gummy worms.

03:57.643 --> 03:59.277
Oh, look,

03:59.279 --> 04:01.980
Jewish and gentile.

04:02.815 --> 04:04.549
I had extra dough.

04:07.521 --> 04:08.687
Oh, that's Leonard.

04:08.689 --> 04:10.088
He said they're about
to cross the border.

04:10.090 --> 04:12.657
I hope the boys don't get
too crazy in Mexico.

04:12.659 --> 04:14.559
Oh, yeah, right.
Lock up your daughters

04:14.561 --> 04:15.894
or Sheldon might
lecture them

04:15.896 --> 04:18.096
about the North American
Free Trade Agreement.

04:19.398 --> 04:22.667
Boy, that was
a long night for me.

04:24.670 --> 04:26.404
Uh-oh.

04:26.406 --> 04:28.807
According to this
Mexican Customs Web site,

04:28.809 --> 04:31.910
visitors may not bring
more than five laser discs,

04:31.912 --> 04:33.812
20 compact discs

04:33.814 --> 04:36.715
or 12 VHS tapes.

04:36.717 --> 04:39.518
We don't have
any of those.

04:39.520 --> 04:41.086
How can you be sure?

04:41.088 --> 04:44.322
VHS was king
when Feynman drove this van.

04:44.324 --> 04:46.291
For all we know,
there are hidden compartments

04:46.293 --> 04:49.127
lousy with Jane Fonda
workout videos.

04:49.129 --> 04:51.329
If there was
a hidden compartment,

04:51.331 --> 04:54.166
don't you think you'd be
stuffed in it by now?

04:55.301 --> 04:58.804
Are we all up to date on our
yellow fever inoculations?

04:58.806 --> 05:02.307
You don't need a yellow fever
shot to go to Mexico.

05:02.309 --> 05:03.775
You can never be too careful.

05:03.777 --> 05:07.012
I got one last year
before I went to Epcot.

05:09.916 --> 05:11.416
So, Penny,
how's married life?

05:11.418 --> 05:12.517
Oh, it's good.

05:12.519 --> 05:14.152
I just wish Leonard
would work up the courage

05:14.154 --> 05:16.721
to tell Sheldon
he's moving in here.

05:16.723 --> 05:18.857
You guys still aren't
living together?

05:18.859 --> 05:20.826
We are. I mean, he sleeps here.

05:20.828 --> 05:22.260
But it's only a matter of time

05:22.262 --> 05:23.595
before Sheldon has a bad dream

05:23.597 --> 05:24.830
and tries to climb into bed

05:24.832 --> 05:27.499
with the Leonard-shaped
pile of pillows.

05:28.367 --> 05:30.135
Speaking of Sheldon,

05:30.137 --> 05:31.369
how's single life treating you?

05:31.371 --> 05:33.171
Fine, I guess.

05:33.173 --> 05:34.739
I've been focusing on me.

05:34.741 --> 05:36.708
I was thinking about
changing my wardrobe.

05:36.710 --> 05:38.810
Yes!
Good for you!

05:39.979 --> 05:42.480
But then I decided I don't want
to go changing who I am

05:42.482 --> 05:43.782
just because of some man.

05:43.784 --> 05:46.651
Yes.
Good for you.

05:47.954 --> 05:49.087
You know, it is normal

05:49.089 --> 05:50.789
to want to change your
look after a breakup.

05:50.791 --> 05:53.625
Actually, I was thinking
of making one small change.

05:53.627 --> 05:54.960
Your sweater?
Your glasses?

05:54.962 --> 05:56.528
Your hair?
Your shoes!

05:56.530 --> 05:58.630
Piercing my ears.

05:58.632 --> 06:00.298
Oh.
Oh.

06:00.300 --> 06:01.766
You really never
had that done?

06:01.768 --> 06:03.235
My mom said pierced ears

06:03.237 --> 06:06.204
were for whores,
pirates and genies.

06:07.406 --> 06:09.875
Okay, well, you're
a grown woman now.

06:09.877 --> 06:12.544
I know, but Sheldon
had this clause

06:12.546 --> 06:13.879
in the Relationship Agreement

06:13.881 --> 06:15.247
forbidding cosmetic surgery

06:15.249 --> 06:17.616
unless it's to look
like a Klingon.

06:19.018 --> 06:20.719
We'll take you to the
mall to get it done.

06:20.721 --> 06:22.287
Why? I can do it
right here.

06:22.289 --> 06:23.321
Really?

06:23.323 --> 06:24.856
You have a piercing gun?
No.

06:24.858 --> 06:26.291
All you need is a needle
and an ice cube.

06:26.293 --> 06:27.626
I've done it, like,
a dozen times.

06:27.628 --> 06:29.194
Oh, I don't know.

06:29.196 --> 06:30.929
Oh, come on.
I'll be gentle.

06:30.931 --> 06:33.098
Let me take your ear virginity.

06:34.634 --> 06:37.469
This party's weird.

06:39.872 --> 06:41.439
Hey, watch your speed.

06:41.441 --> 06:42.974
I hear the Mexican police
target tourists.

06:42.976 --> 06:44.943
Oh, not a problem.

06:44.945 --> 06:46.111
If anything goes down,

06:46.113 --> 06:47.879
we just put Koothrappali
in the driver's seat

06:47.881 --> 06:50.882
and slap a sombrero
on his head.

06:50.884 --> 06:54.686
Dude, how many races can you
offend in a single breath?

06:54.688 --> 06:55.820
I don't know.

06:55.822 --> 06:58.056
Have you watched
the Olympics with me?

06:59.158 --> 07:01.359
Sheldon, can you believe
that we're driving in a van

07:01.361 --> 07:03.361
that was owned by one of
the greatest scientific minds

07:03.363 --> 07:05.096
of the 20th century?

07:05.098 --> 07:06.498
It's like the Batmobile.

07:07.233 --> 07:08.867
If Batman was real

07:08.869 --> 07:10.335
and a physicist

07:10.337 --> 07:13.071
and his car wasn't cool.

07:13.073 --> 07:14.940
It is extraordinary.

07:14.942 --> 07:17.943
Perhaps some of his mojo
will rub off on us.

07:17.945 --> 07:20.345
Maybe between this
and his beach house,

07:20.347 --> 07:22.447
we will be inspired
to greatness.

07:22.449 --> 07:25.583
I usually don't put too much
stock in charms and talismans.

07:25.585 --> 07:27.018
However, even I must admit

07:27.020 --> 07:28.620
feeling Richard Feynman's

07:28.622 --> 07:32.223
butt dent cupping
my own bottom...

07:32.225 --> 07:35.060
that does get
the creative juices flowing.

07:36.429 --> 07:38.096
Hey, I have to return this van.

07:38.098 --> 07:40.532
Keep your creative juices
in your pants.

07:42.235 --> 07:43.301
What was that?

07:43.303 --> 07:44.936
I think it's a tire.

07:44.938 --> 07:47.439
What if it's banditos
shooting at us?

07:47.441 --> 07:48.807
What if we get kidnapped?

07:48.809 --> 07:51.476
What if we end up in a factory
making Bart Simpson piñatas

07:51.478 --> 07:53.745
for the rest of our lives?!

07:53.747 --> 07:55.914
It's the tire.

07:56.782 --> 07:57.916
Leonard?

07:57.918 --> 07:58.950
What?

07:58.952 --> 08:01.519
I am getting too old
for this crud.

08:04.523 --> 08:07.092
Amy, I noticed
your status still says

08:07.094 --> 08:09.527
"in a relationship"
on Facebook.

08:09.529 --> 08:10.962
You're right.

08:10.964 --> 08:13.164
I should probably let
all of my Facebook friends know.

08:13.166 --> 08:16.935
Penny, I'm no longer
in a relationship.

08:18.471 --> 08:20.638
Did you change yours
to "married" yet?

08:20.640 --> 08:22.073
Uh, no, not yet.

08:22.075 --> 08:24.109
There's still a few people
I haven't told personally.

08:24.111 --> 08:25.176
Who?

08:25.178 --> 08:26.678
Oh, just my parents

08:26.680 --> 08:28.179
and my entire family.

08:28.181 --> 08:29.948
What?

08:29.950 --> 08:31.016
Why?

08:31.018 --> 08:32.450
Well, I don't want
to hurt my dad.

08:32.452 --> 08:33.650
You know, he always wanted

08:33.653 --> 08:35.320
to dance with his daughter
at her wedding.

08:35.322 --> 08:36.855
What about
your sister's wedding?

08:36.857 --> 08:39.823
They started to,
then her water broke.

08:40.993 --> 08:42.894
You know, if he finds out
we eloped,

08:42.895 --> 08:44.062
it's gonna break his heart.

08:44.063 --> 08:45.897
How long do you think
you can keep it from him?

08:45.899 --> 08:48.733
Yeah, isn't it gonna get
worse the longer you wait?

08:48.735 --> 08:50.268
Well, not necessarily.

08:50.270 --> 08:52.103
You know,
Dad's not getting any younger,

08:52.105 --> 08:53.705
so if I wait long enough,

08:53.707 --> 08:55.473
I'll just tell him
he walked me down the aisle

08:55.475 --> 08:57.008
and it was magical.

09:02.148 --> 09:04.315
When did you learn
how to change a tire?

09:04.317 --> 09:06.684
Every self-respecting gentleman
should know how

09:06.686 --> 09:08.987
in case he comes across
a damsel in distress

09:08.989 --> 09:10.488
by the side of the road.

09:11.824 --> 09:12.991
If I see one scorpion,

09:12.993 --> 09:14.359
I am getting
on someone's shoulders

09:14.361 --> 09:16.394
and never coming down.

09:16.396 --> 09:18.630
And there's your damsel.

09:19.965 --> 09:22.333
Wow, this one's really stuck.

09:22.335 --> 09:23.968
Are you turning
it the right way?

09:23.970 --> 09:25.537
No.

09:25.539 --> 09:26.805
I took the other four off

09:26.807 --> 09:28.339
and when I got to this one,
I thought,

09:28.341 --> 09:30.208
"You know, I'm in a rut.
Let's shake things up."

09:30.210 --> 09:32.077
Here, let me try.

09:38.551 --> 09:41.319
You're right, it doesn't turn
the other way.

