Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

09:52.259 --> 09:53.761
There you go.

09:53.762 --> 09:54.727
You're all done!

09:54.729 --> 09:56.162
That wasn't so bad.

09:57.465 --> 09:59.065
Nice.

09:59.067 --> 10:01.067
Boy, if my mom could see me now,

10:01.069 --> 10:03.670
she'd lock me in the sin closet.

10:05.739 --> 10:07.173
That's a joke, right?

10:07.175 --> 10:08.875
Actually, the joke was on her.

10:08.877 --> 10:10.977
I could still see the TV
through the slats.

10:12.046 --> 10:13.546
I'm starting to see

10:13.548 --> 10:15.615
why you and your mom
aren't very close.

10:16.383 --> 10:17.517
Bet she'd still tell her

10:17.519 --> 10:18.618
if she got married.

10:18.620 --> 10:20.587
You're not gonna
let this go, are you?

10:20.589 --> 10:22.522
Well, it's kind of sad
that they don't know.

10:22.524 --> 10:24.157
I mean, they love Leonard.

10:24.159 --> 10:25.425
Fine, you want
me to call?

10:25.427 --> 10:26.559
I'll call.

10:28.129 --> 10:29.696
Why am I so nervous?

10:29.698 --> 10:30.964
It's understandable.

10:30.966 --> 10:33.700
Amy was afraid to tell her mom
she broke up with Sheldon.

10:33.702 --> 10:34.868
Yeah?
How did it go?

10:34.870 --> 10:36.135
Did she make you crawl

10:36.137 --> 10:37.670
into the breaking-up drawer?

10:39.306 --> 10:40.907
Uh, well, actually,
to be honest...

10:40.909 --> 10:42.467
I-I haven't told her yet.

10:42.468 --> 10:44.235
You've been giving me
a hard time

10:44.236 --> 10:46.203
and you haven't even told
your mom about Sheldon?

10:46.573 --> 10:48.372
I'm feeling a little dizzy
from all the blood loss.

10:48.373 --> 10:50.006
I don't know
what you're talking about.

10:52.076 --> 10:53.810
Fine. I'm calling home,

10:53.812 --> 10:55.312
but when I'm done,
you're calling your mother.

10:55.314 --> 10:57.447
Easy for you to say.

10:57.449 --> 10:59.749
You never had to watch
<i>60 Minutes</i> like this.

11:02.353 --> 11:03.520
Hey, Daddy.

11:03.522 --> 11:04.788
Hey, slugger.

11:04.790 --> 11:06.189
How's my girl?

11:06.191 --> 11:07.824
Uh, good. Is Mom around?

11:07.826 --> 11:09.926
Ah, she took your brother out
to celebrate.

11:09.928 --> 11:12.796
He just got his tenth
one-month sober chip.

11:13.998 --> 11:17.767
Yeah, she's gonna make him
a little necklace.

11:17.769 --> 11:19.236
Okay, I'll talk to her later.

11:19.238 --> 11:21.071
Uh, Dad, there's something
I need to tell you.

11:21.706 --> 11:24.207
Leonard and I got married.

11:24.209 --> 11:25.375
You did?

11:25.377 --> 11:26.710
When?

11:26.712 --> 11:28.378
Last week. I'm sorry,
I should've told you.

11:28.380 --> 11:29.746
It was a spur
of the moment thing.

11:29.748 --> 11:30.981
I feel terrible.

11:30.983 --> 11:32.349
Please don't be
too disappointed.

11:32.351 --> 11:34.551
Are you happy?

11:34.553 --> 11:35.552
Very.

11:35.554 --> 11:36.853
Leonard is so great.

11:36.855 --> 11:38.688
Well, then I'm happy for you.

11:38.690 --> 11:40.890
Aw, thank you, Daddy.

11:40.892 --> 11:41.958
That means so much.

11:41.960 --> 11:43.260
Well, I understand it's hard

11:43.262 --> 11:44.494
to tell someone something

11:44.496 --> 11:46.429
if you think
it's gonna upset 'em.

11:46.431 --> 11:47.664
It is.

11:47.666 --> 11:49.065
You're the best dad ever.

11:49.067 --> 11:52.569
Yeah. Uh, hold that thought.

11:52.571 --> 11:54.904
I've been sitting
on a little news myself.

11:54.906 --> 11:56.539
Well, what is it?

11:56.541 --> 11:59.709
You know that rototiller
I got for the tractor?

11:59.711 --> 12:00.777
No.

12:00.779 --> 12:01.811
Oh, you should see it.

12:01.813 --> 12:04.481
It is a beautiful
piece of machinery.

12:04.483 --> 12:07.217
Anyway, uh...

12:07.219 --> 12:10.186
I backed over
your pet pig with it.

12:10.188 --> 12:12.689
Moondance?

12:12.691 --> 12:15.925
Yeah, he's, uh,
not dancing anymore.

12:15.927 --> 12:17.894
You killed my pig?

12:18.929 --> 12:20.130
I did not kill him.

12:20.132 --> 12:22.465
The vet took care of that.

12:22.467 --> 12:24.200
When?

12:24.202 --> 12:27.270
Oh... ten, 12 months ago.

12:28.606 --> 12:29.973
You didn't tell me for a year?!

12:29.975 --> 12:32.442
Well, apple doesn't fall far
from the tree, does it?

12:33.477 --> 12:34.644
Love ya, slugger.

12:34.646 --> 12:36.313
Gotta go!

12:38.749 --> 12:40.950
Okay, Amy, your turn.

12:50.494 --> 12:52.662
What are you doing?

12:52.664 --> 12:54.631
It's called Lamaze breathing.

12:54.633 --> 12:57.267
It helps you push.

12:58.102 --> 12:59.369
Great.

12:59.371 --> 13:00.770
He's pushing
with his uterus.

13:03.040 --> 13:05.909
There's got to be a smarter way
of removing it.

13:05.911 --> 13:07.677
Yeah, this is nothing more
than a physics problem.

13:07.679 --> 13:08.945
Right.

13:08.947 --> 13:10.714
Archimedes once said,

13:10.716 --> 13:11.981
"Give me a 'leever' long enough

13:11.983 --> 13:13.483
"and a fulcrum
on which to place it,

13:13.485 --> 13:14.818
and I shall move the world."

13:14.820 --> 13:16.519
Of course.

13:16.521 --> 13:18.221
All we need is to find stuff

13:18.223 --> 13:20.724
to make a "leever" big
enough to fix this.

13:20.726 --> 13:21.958
Exactly.

13:21.960 --> 13:23.126
I'll bet there's
something around here

13:23.128 --> 13:24.728
that could
be a "lehver."

13:24.730 --> 13:27.163
Let's see, a "lehver,"
a "lehver"...

13:27.165 --> 13:28.565
Everybody hold on!

13:28.567 --> 13:30.300
Let's take this problem
one step at a time.

13:30.302 --> 13:31.968
First, we need to decide

13:31.970 --> 13:34.270
whether we're calling it
leever or lehver.

13:36.240 --> 13:38.174
And the sooner
we decide it's leever,

13:38.176 --> 13:41.044
the sooner we can roll up
our sleeves-- not slehves--

13:41.046 --> 13:42.712
and get to work.

13:42.714 --> 13:44.614
We're gonna be here
"foreever."

13:48.285 --> 13:49.719
Thanks a lot, guys.

13:49.721 --> 13:50.787
What did we do?

13:50.789 --> 13:52.055
Before I made that call,

13:52.057 --> 13:53.356
my pig was alive and happy

13:53.358 --> 13:54.691
and rolling around in the mud.

13:54.693 --> 13:57.060
Now he's illegally buried
in our backyard

13:57.062 --> 13:59.362
next to my great-grandmother.

13:59.364 --> 14:01.598
Really?

14:01.600 --> 14:04.501
They didn't eat him?

14:04.503 --> 14:06.369
No.

14:06.371 --> 14:09.038
He was a beloved member
of the family.

14:09.040 --> 14:12.108
The breakfast meat family?

14:13.878 --> 14:15.311
It's not funny.

14:15.313 --> 14:16.780
You're up.
Call your mother.

14:16.782 --> 14:18.281
Oh, maybe later.

14:18.283 --> 14:21.017
Your pig dying
made me sad.

14:21.019 --> 14:23.019
And a little hungry.

14:23.021 --> 14:24.521
Phone, now.

14:24.523 --> 14:26.222
Okay. Okay.

14:26.224 --> 14:27.857
Fine.

14:30.628 --> 14:31.995
Hi, Mom.

14:31.997 --> 14:33.329
Try dialing.

14:35.032 --> 14:36.866
You saw that, huh?

14:40.771 --> 14:43.139
Hi, Mom. How are you doing?

14:44.375 --> 14:45.608
Oh, good.

14:45.610 --> 14:47.243
How's work?

14:47.245 --> 14:48.211
That's nice.

14:48.213 --> 14:49.612
I'm fine.

14:49.614 --> 14:51.748
Hey, listen,
I've been meaning to ask,

14:51.750 --> 14:55.151
how come Aunt Doe and
Aunt Florence never got along?

14:55.153 --> 14:56.519
Okay, just...
give me that.

14:56.521 --> 14:58.021
Amy broke up with Sheldon,

14:58.023 --> 14:59.088
she got her ears pierced

14:59.090 --> 15:01.658
and she made us
eat penis cookies!

15:04.728 --> 15:05.962
Hang on.

15:05.964 --> 15:07.997
She wants to talk to you.

15:12.236 --> 15:14.137
I don't think
the lever's working.

15:14.139 --> 15:15.705
What makes you say that?

15:20.678 --> 15:23.413
There's gotta be
something else we could try.

15:23.415 --> 15:25.348
If this was <i>Star</i> <i>Trek,</i>

15:25.350 --> 15:27.517
we could use a phaser
to blast it off.

15:27.519 --> 15:29.385
No, it's too
broad of a beam.

15:29.387 --> 15:30.987
You'd need something
more precise,

15:30.989 --> 15:32.989
like Superman's heat vision.

15:32.991 --> 15:34.324
Ooh, the Green
Lantern's ring

15:34.326 --> 15:36.426
could make a big green
hand that unscrews it.

15:36.428 --> 15:37.961
If you need
a green hand,

15:37.963 --> 15:39.229
why not just
use the Hulk?

15:39.231 --> 15:40.797
Oh, please, the Hulk
would never get

15:40.799 --> 15:42.999
across the border
with that temper.

15:43.001 --> 15:44.601
Guys, excuse me,

15:44.603 --> 15:46.569
not that calling
one of the Avengers

15:46.571 --> 15:48.805
isn't a perfectly
reasonable choice,

15:48.807 --> 15:49.939
but we're
scientists.

15:49.941 --> 15:51.608
Don't you think we
can figure this out

15:51.610 --> 15:52.976
using actual science?

15:52.978 --> 15:55.011
Yes, we could
use science.

15:55.013 --> 15:56.279
But it's your
bachelor party.

15:56.281 --> 15:57.680
Lighten up.

16:12.029 --> 16:13.930
♪ We will ♪

16:13.932 --> 16:17.066
♪ We will
percussive shock you ♪

16:17.835 --> 16:19.702
♪ We will ♪

16:19.704 --> 16:22.105
♪ We will
percussive shock you ♪

16:23.774 --> 16:25.108
♪ Buddy you're a boy ♪

16:25.110 --> 16:26.576
♪ Make a big noise ♪

16:26.578 --> 16:27.810
♪ Playin' in the street ♪

16:27.812 --> 16:29.579
♪ Gonna be a big man someday ♪

16:29.581 --> 16:32.382
♪ You got mud on your face,
you big disgrace ♪

16:32.384 --> 16:35.318
♪ Kickin' your can
all over the place. ♪

16:40.224 --> 16:41.724
I have an eidetic memory.

16:41.726 --> 16:43.192
Sometimes it's a curse.

16:48.198 --> 16:50.233
I had no idea

16:50.235 --> 16:51.935
tortilla chips were
such a good fuel source.

16:51.937 --> 16:55.838
They're basically pure
hydrocarbons soaked in fat.

16:55.840 --> 16:57.807
Let's hope the lug nut expands.

16:57.809 --> 17:00.043
What if that burning
food attracts animals?

17:00.045 --> 17:02.178
We have plenty of food
for the animals.

17:02.180 --> 17:03.546
- We do?
- Yep.

17:03.548 --> 17:06.249
A six-foot wiener
in a Flash T-shirt.

17:06.251 --> 17:08.685
That's not very nice.

17:08.686 --> 17:10.553
It's a bachelor party.
Lighten up.

17:15.593 --> 17:18.595
What is that awful smell?

17:18.597 --> 17:19.829
It's burning salsa.

17:19.830 --> 17:21.564
I'm hoping the acidity
and salinity

17:21.566 --> 17:23.633
combined with electricity
will corrode the lug nut off.

17:23.635 --> 17:26.169
What an innovative solution.

17:26.171 --> 17:29.606
Perhaps I don't give your
MIT education enough credit.

17:29.608 --> 17:32.075
Yeah, I saw it on <i>Mythbusters.</i>

17:37.314 --> 17:40.049
All right, this rust,

17:40.051 --> 17:42.852
combined with the aluminum
recovered from the van,

17:42.854 --> 17:44.454
is now thermite.

17:44.456 --> 17:45.455
Great.

17:45.457 --> 17:47.590
Couple pinches
ought to do the trick.

17:47.592 --> 17:49.559
Is that enough
to melt the lug nut?

17:49.561 --> 17:50.526
Well, let's start small.

17:50.528 --> 17:51.561
We can always add more.

17:51.563 --> 17:54.497
You put up a good fight,
lug nut,

17:54.499 --> 17:58.201
but you've met your match.

18:15.586 --> 18:16.819
Hey, look!

18:16.821 --> 18:19.522
The lug nut's off.

18:36.705 --> 18:38.172
What...

18:38.174 --> 18:40.307
What are you
doing back?

18:42.444 --> 18:43.844
We got a flat

18:43.846 --> 18:45.145
and couldn't get
the tire off.

18:45.147 --> 18:46.980
Oh, I'm sorry.

18:46.982 --> 18:48.315
Thank you.

18:48.317 --> 18:49.783
If it makes you feel any better,

18:49.785 --> 18:51.085
I pierced Amy's ears

18:51.087 --> 18:53.854
and her mom made her sit
in my closet.

18:58.159 --> 18:59.693
We blew up Feynman's van.

18:59.695 --> 19:02.262
My dad killed my pig
with his tractor.

19:02.264 --> 19:04.698
I spent the night
in Mexico with Sheldon.

19:04.700 --> 19:06.033
You win.

